                        "content": "The nurse is assessing the respiratory status of a client who has suffered a fractured rib. The nurse would expect to note which finding?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nRib fractures result from a blunt injury or a fall. Typical signs and symptoms include pain and tenderness localized at the fracture site that is exacerbated by inspiration and palpation, shallow respirations, splinting or guarding the chest protectively to minimize chest movement, and possible bruising at the fracture site. Paradoxical respirations are seen with flail chest.",
                        "id": "26b13660219d45a6abcfd3e08e5e29c6",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1cdc487779854000a5eefbf645e7e3ca",
                                "content": "Strapping is useful only if the ribs are fractured in several places at once."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e32ca2faa8014612842689f074125eaa",
                                "content": "That's a good idea. I'll ask the doctor for a prescription for the needed supplies."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "66d6aeb543e54f94ae1a00744cdba472",
                                "content": "That isn't done because people often would develop pneumonia from the constricting effect on the lungs."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "94d10b149dfd47ab80b0bd6594f84e24",
                                "content": "That might help you to breathe better, but this facility does not carry the necessary supplies in the stockroom. When you get home, you can purchase them at the medical supply store."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "1cdc487779854000a5eefbf645e7e3ca",
