                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A chest x-ray report for a client indicates the presence of a left apical pneumothorax. The nurse would assess the status of breath sounds in that area by placing the stethoscope in which location?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe apex of the lung is the rounded, uppermost part of the lung. Therefore, the nurse would place the stethoscope just under the left clavicle. All of the other options are incorrect locations for assessing the left apex.",
                        "id": "98e17d4adae54abfa05ada3fecef7865",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d73640e93742421c9a22ebf7b8cb1a54",
                                "content": "A low respiratory rate"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a84e28bacb2f4ac1bb265712e49e644b",
                                "content": "Diminished breath sounds"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "129eaa9a5f4c48239d13dd9b58cc2cc1",
                                "content": "The presence of a barrel chest"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "1db7f8f91fde4aa5a3f6118f07dac815",
                                "content": "A sucking sound at the site of injury"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "d73640e93742421c9a22ebf7b8cb1a54",
                                    "content": "A low respiratory rate"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "a84e28bacb2f4ac1bb265712e49e644b",
                                    "content": "Diminished breath sounds"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "129eaa9a5f4c48239d13dd9b58cc2cc1",
                                    "content": "The presence of a barrel chest"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "1db7f8f91fde4aa5a3f6118f07dac815",
                                    "content": "A sucking sound at the site of injury"
                                }
                            ]
                        },
